Subject: Maltese Amoeba? (PC)

A friend approached me the other day to ask if I new anything about
the virus Maltese Amoeba. Not being a virus expert (or one who has
ever had to consider such things, our Centre deals with it) I could
not answer. However, on asking `our man' he could not help either, so
I turn to you... I am also not a regular reader of this group so
please cc. any replies to me.

The only details she had were:

1) It is believed to have originated in Malta (hence the name!)
and been passed to their system.

2) It was detected when the disk space was used by an unknown source,
and no other programs could be run. There has been no further
disaster with it but they are obviously concerned.

3) It was detected just after Christmas but they have only ever heard of
one other occurrence of it.

I have scanned the current postings for any details on it but the
only reference I've seen is a query like mine and that perhaps its
alias is Irish Virus.

So if you can help, all suggestions would be appreciated.
Thanks in advance,

