Date:    Sat, 08 Feb 92 05:09:14 -0400
From:    calhoun@ihost.isnet.com (Warren D. Calhoun)
Subject: Re: Help: 1193 virus? (PC)

frisk@complex.is (Fridrik Skulason) writes:

>In Message 29 Jan 92 19:31:54 GMT,
>  mark@walt.CS.MsState.Edu (Mark Rauschkolb) writes:

>>I was just asked if I knew anything about the 1193 virus.  I can't
>>find a reference to it anywhere.  Any clues?

>I don't recognize any virus with that name, but there is one which is
>1193 bytes long - namely the "Copyright" virus....

>I haven't analysed it in detail, so I don't have any useful information on
>it.

I haven't analyzed it either, but we had it hit a series of machines
in the offices where I work.  It was provided (free of charge) by a
clone systems manufacturer along with some public domain/shareware
stuff (and also the Jerusalem virus).  The apparent symptoms are that
an infected executeable will not run (giving a 'cannot execute' error
or something to that effect) the first time an attempt is made, and
will be deleted either at that time or the next time an attempt is
made to run it.  It is reported by some virus detection software as
the 1193 virus (due to it's size) but is now more commonly known as
the Copyright virus (I don't know why).  It is reported to infect .COM
files (including COMMAND.COM, load itself into RAM and remain
resident, and directly or indirectly corrupts file linkages.  More
info (and removal procedures) can be had from McAfee Associates anti-
virus products.

